    }, {
        "@context": "http://schema.org",
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [{
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What can I expect to accomplish after completing the PRINCE2 Foundation course?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The <b>PRINCE2 Foundation course online</b> is the first of the two PRINCE2 courses, thoughtfully designed to help you get started on your journey as a Project Manager. You will be equipped with the knowledge and expertise to:&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Make your foray into the field of project management and projects&nbsp;</li><li>Effectively handle projects in diverse environments&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Achieve a higher likelihood of project success&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Improve efficiency at your workplace&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Deliver successful projects on time and within budget&nbsp;</li><li>Fine tune PRINCE to different project circumstances&nbsp;</li><li>Guide a project from initiation to completion&nbsp;</li></ul>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What practical skills can I expect to have after completing the PRINCE2 Foundation course?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The <b>PRINCE2 Foundation course online</b> aims to equip you with the skills needed to get started on a PRINCE2 project management career. You will be able to:&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Apply and tailor the PRINCE2 method to diverse projects&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Bring in project flexibility&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Apply the seven PRINCE2 principles, processes and themes to projects&nbsp; &nbsp;</li><li>Understand the fundamentals of the PRINCE2 principles&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Provide business justification for the project&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Build on experience from previous projects&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Understand project roles and responsibilities&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Manage a project by breaking it into chunks&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Understand the different activities involved in the PRINCE2 Processes, from starting a project to guiding it through completion&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Start a project by giving necessary justifications for it&nbsp;</li><li>Direct the project with key decisions&nbsp;</li><li>Initiate project progress by understanding all aspects of strategies need to be applied and creation of products&nbsp;</li><li>Understand how to bring the project under control through the Controlling&nbsp; stage process&nbsp;</li><li>Monitor the project and keep it under defined controls&nbsp;</li><li>Communicate project progress to stakeholders&nbsp;</li><li>Apply PRINCE2 principles to close a project&nbsp;<br></li><li>Check if the project has achieved all objectives&nbsp;</li><li>Deliver product to the customer</li></ul>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Is PRINCE2 Foundation certification worth doing?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>Yes, The <b>PRINCE2 Foundation certification</b> will help you in a variety of ways:</p><ul><li>Validate your commitment to continued excellence and quality&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Get started on a career in project management&nbsp; &nbsp;</li><li>Demonstrate your understanding of the PRINCE2 framework&nbsp; &nbsp;</li><li>Gain project management best practices and grow your career with confidence&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Work across diverse projects and challenging work environments&nbsp; &nbsp;</li><li>Command higher salaries than your non-certified peers&nbsp; &nbsp;</li><li>Improve your employment prospects&nbsp;</li></ul>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Is this PRINCE2 Foundation course only for software professionals?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<ul><li>Not necessarily. The workshop is aimed at project managers, aspiring project managers and anyone who manages projects. <b>PRINCE2 Foundation course</b> can be taken by Novices and aspiring project managers or professionals who are part of a PM team and would like to get certified.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Anyone who is looking to develop project management skills, such as&nbsp;</li><li>Project Board members (e.g. Senior Responsible Owners)&nbsp;</li><li>Team Managers (e.g. Product Delivery Managers)&nbsp;<br></li><li>Project Assurance (e.g. Business Change Analysts)&nbsp;<br></li><li>Project Support (e.g. Project and Programme Office personnel)&nbsp;<br></li><li>Operational line managers or staff.&nbsp;<br></li></ul>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What are the prerequisites to attend PRINCE2 Foundation course online?  ",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>Basic experience with projects in a real-world context is helpful, though not mandatory.<br></p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What next after PRINCE2 Foundation?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>Once you have gained the PRINCE 2 FOUNDATION, you can consider learning:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>PRINCE2 PRACTITIONER&nbsp;</li><li>PRINCE2 AGILE CERTIFICATION&nbsp;</li><li>Project Management Professional (PMP)&nbsp;</li></ul>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How many PDUs will I be eligible for?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>You will be eligible for 16 PDUs on course completion that can be used for recertification from PMI Inc.<br></p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Where are PDUs applicable?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>PDUs recognize your dedication to the Agile world through the award of credits for every educational effort you make throughout your career. PDUs are offered by the PMI, and every PMI certification, except the CAPM, requires you to earn a specific number of PDUs per three-year certification cycle. &nbsp;<br></p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Do I need to renew my PRINCE2 Foundation certification?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>No, the PRINCE2 Foundation certification has lifetime validity.&nbsp;<br></p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How long does a PRINCE2 Foundation course take?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p><b>PRINCE2 Foundation course online</b> training involves 16 hours of trainer-led sessions. You can opt to write the exam directly, but it is recommended that you take this training and prepare for a few weeks for the PRINCE2 Foundation Exam. You get certified on clearing the exam.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is PRINCE2 Foundation 6th edition?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>In <b>PRINCE2 Foundation</b> 6th Edition you will learn updated concepts of project management in the PRINCE2 framework, familiarize yourself with the principles, themes, and terminology of PRINCE2.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Is PRINCE2 Foundation a qualification?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
