                "text": "<p>Yes, <b>PRINCE2 Foundation</b> is a certification that validates your understanding of the PRINCE2 framework and the fundamentals of project management.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Who provides the PRINCE2 Foundation certification?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>All PRINCE2 foundation certifications are offered by AXELOS, which is the accrediting body for PRINCE2 foundation certification.&nbsp;<br></p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can I get certified without taking the PRINCE2 Foundation Certification course?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>You can self-study and take the examination directly through an AXELOS Examination Institute like PeopleCert®  without attending an accredited training course, for a PRINCE2 Foundation certification.</p><p>However, undertaking a formalized training program through an Accredited Training Organization (ATO) like KnowledgeHut highly increases your chances of being successful in the exam. Most importantly, beyond providing extensive exam preparation, the training will equip you with real-world skills and help you stand out among your peers.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How do I become PRINCE2 Foundation certified?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<div>Here are the steps you should follow to <b>become PRINCE2 Foundation certified</b>:&nbsp;</div><ol><li>Fulfill the eligibility requirements.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></li><li>Decide whether to self-study or get trained by an Accredited Training Organization (ATO). When you enrol for KnowledgeHut's <b>PRINCE2 Foundation Certification Training</b>, you're in for an immersive learning experience that will help you acquire immediately applicable project management skills. You'll get industry-ready and benefit from comprehensive support throughout your exam preparation and certification journey.</li><li>Complete the two-day training with KnowledgeHut.</li><li>Take advantage of KnowledgeHut's comprehensive exam support: practice papers, one-to-one mentoring and more. Read the study materials to get a complete understanding of the PRINCE2 methodology and concepts. ‘Managing Successful Projects with PRINCE2. 6th Edition’ is one of the most important reference materials for your preparation. Practice extensively.</li><li>If you have decided to self-study, schedule the exam through PeopleCert. If you have enrolled with KnowledgeHut, we will schedule the exam on a date suitable for you. You can take the test online via PeopleCert Online Proctoring or at a Training Organization convenient for you. All you need is a PC or Mac computer and an internet connection. </li><li>If you're taking the exam at a training organization near you, you will need to carry with you: (1) a print-out of the exam schedule from PeopleCert; (2) Proof of identity like passport, driving license.</li><li>You'll get to see your preliminary result on your computer screen instantly on completing your test. Your official results/e-certificate will be issued by PeopleCert within 2 business days. You'll then be able to see your result and download your certificate.</li><li>Download your certificate from your PeopleCert profile after two business days of completing the exam.</li></ol><div>On passing the exam, AXELOS will send you an email regarding the My AXELOS membership and how you can activate it. Complete the yearly requirement of 20 CPDs so that you can get a digital badge that reflects your achievement. The certificate expires after 3 years. Renew your certification by taking the Practitioner exam again or by maintaining the CPD requirements.<br></div>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How long does it take to get PRINCE2 Foundation certified?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>You will need to attend 16-hours of <b>PRINCE2 Foundation Training online</b> from an ATO of AXELOS and PeopleCert®, following which you will be required to take an exam to demonstrate your knowledge of PRINCE2 in order to get certified.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>The result of your test is issued within 2 business days from the date of your exam. If you pass the PRINCE2 Foundation exam with the required score, you will also receive an e-certificate along with official results. Both the official results and the e-certificate will be uploaded on your PeopleCert® Account.&nbsp;</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the My PRINCE2 Subscription?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>My PRINCE2 subscription is for all professionals in the field of project management who want to use practical help, easy-access support, and professional endorsement to advance their careers. With the My PRINCE2 subscription, you will also have access to the following:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>CPD toolset to keep your certificate up-to-date&nbsp;</li><li>Discounts to some of the AXELOS best practice publications&nbsp;</li><li>Exclusive white papers&nbsp;</li><li>PRINCE2. 6th edition templates&nbsp;</li><li>PRINCE2. 6th edition and PRINCE2 Agile official online guidance</li></ul>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What does My PRINCE2 subscription cost?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>A <b>My PRINCE2&nbsp;</b>subscription will cost about £50 +VAT. If you subscribe for another year, the cost of the second subscription will be £30 (+VAT) and for a third subscription, the price will be £20 (+VAT) per annum.&nbsp;</p><p>Once you reach the end of your subscription after 12 months, you will receive a reminder for subscription renewal before the expiry date. Failure to renew your subscription will lead to the removal of access from the latest publications, digital badges, CPD activities, and best practices available as a part of the product subscription. If you renew your subscription after the expiry date has passed and your subscription has lapsed, just log back in and pay the new subscription fee.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Is My PRINCE2 a paid subscription or is it free?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
